-- BP Seeks $3.4 Billion Cut in Potential Oil Spill Fine
-- B y   L a u r e l   B r u b a k e r   C a l k i n s
-- 2013-01-11T19:53:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-11/bp-seeks-3-4-billion-cut-in-potential-oil-spill-fine.html
BP Plc (BP/)  is seeking a reduction of as
much as $3.4 billion in the fine it may have to pay for
pollution caused by the 2010 Gulf of Mexico oil spill.  The company wants credit for collecting 800,000 barrels of
spilled oil, according to a court filing. London-based BP is
facing a maximum fine of more than $20 billion.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Dunn at 
 adunn8@bloomberg.net  